title: About 'Sister Wives' Meri Brown's Friend Jenn Sullivan - Distractify
content:
The Gist: Meri Brown from 'Sister Wives' has a best friend named Jenn Sullivan.

The two host a "Fridays With Friends" live stream on Meri's Instagram account.

Fans think there's more to their relationship.

Article continues below advertisement

The cast of the hit TLC series Sister Wives is constantly changing. With Kody Brown, his wife Robyn, his three ex-wives, and their 18 children, the family is growing or shrinking each and every day.

But, there are a few non-family members who also make appearances on the show. One that fans are slowly starting to get to know is Jenn Sullivan. Does Meri Brown's friend help out the family? Here is everything to know about her.

Article continues below advertisement

Jenn Sullivan is a friend of 'Sister Wives' star Meri Brown — but is that it?

Outside of the popular reality TV show, Meri Brown owns Lizzie's Heritage Inn, a bed and breakfast located in Utah. The hotel is managed by her very close friend Jenn Sullivan. So, they are business partners as well as friends. There are rumors about their relationship beyond this, but we'll get to that in a moment.

Article continues below advertisement

First, you should know that when they are not working at the inn, Meri and Jenn host a "Fridays With Friends" livestream on Meri's Instagram account every week to discuss a variety of topics.

Sometimes, they even share weird stories from the inn, and believe it or not, they are both convinced that the hotel is haunted. Jenn has claimed that the TV flicks on and off without anyone touching a remote. Meri has stated that a ghost is most likely her mother who passed away.

Article continues below advertisement

This segment has been a great way for fans to get to know the family friend on a more personal level. Jenn's Instagram handle is @justjennreally, but her account is currently private with nearly 5,000 followers.

Jenn Sullivan and Meri Brown had a drinking controversy.

Article continues below advertisement

Most of the time, the ladeis' Instagram live sessions are great fun and harmless. But, there was one incident during one of their live streams in April 2023 when the two of them couldn't stop laughing and mispronouncing the names of fans who tuned in.

Even though they claimed to be just tired, viewers weren't buying that at all and were starting to get concerned. One person even commented and asked them what they were smoking.

Article continues below advertisement

"The two of us aren't smoking anything. I've heard that stuff kills brain cells," Jenn responded. Meri also clapped back at the fan. Nevertheless, both of them are adults and should be allowed to get tipsy (or engage in legal activities of their choice), even if they aren't willing to admit it to the public.

Fans believe that Jenn Sullivan and Meri Brown are a couple.

Article continues below advertisement

Based on the fact that they spend a lot of time together and work together, fans are starting to speculate whether or not the two are together romantically.

title: Janelle and Meri Brown's friendship under scrutiny as 'Sister Wives' star skips out on co-star's BNB - MEAWW
content:
Janelle Brown and Meri Brown's friendship under scrutiny as 'Sister Wives' star skips out on co-star's BNB

'Sister Wives' stars Janelle Brown and Meri Brown are no longer in a spiritual marriage with Kody Brown

FLAGSTAFF, ARIZONA: It seems like 'Sister Wives' stars Janelle and Meri Brown haven't been on good terms since the two weren't seen posting much about each other on social media ever since they separated from Kody Brown.

Janelle's recent post adds to the speculation as it hints that there might be something wrong between the TLC co-stars.

'Sister Wives' star Janelle Brown and Meri Brown's alleged fallout drags on (Instagram/@janellebrown117)

Janelle Brown skips out on Meri Brown's BNB

Janelle recently posted about her trip to Kanab, Utah. And, to everyone's astonishment, she did not stay at Meri's Bed and Breakfast.

Janelle captioned the post, "Whenever I’m traveling through Kanab, UT I try and stay at this cute refurbished retro boutique hotel." She added, "@quailparklodge Something about it just makes me happy. It’s unique. Not like every other hotel I stay in."

TLC star then added, "As it seems my life has more travel these days I’m always on the lookout for these gems. If you stay at one or have one near you would you drop the name and city in the comments?"

As Janelle posted a bunch of photos on Instagram about where she stayed when in Kanab, a user commented, "Do you ever stay at Meri’s B&B?" "What about meri brown bnb," another commented.

'Sister Wives' star Janelle Brown shares a glimpse into her Kanab, Utah trip (Instagram/@janellebrown117)

A user compared the photos Janelle shared with that of Meri's B&B, saying, "It's looks better than Meris B & B."

Another speculated, "Going to a bridal shower, possibly?" A user claimed, "So where are you hanging your hat these days, or have you become a professional wanderer?"

Did 'Sister Wives' star Kody Brown accuse Janelle Brown of cheating?

Kody Brown slammed Janelle Brown (Instagram/@kodywinnbrown)

In the recently released episode of 'Sister Wives' Season 18, Kody and Janelle's argument turned heated. As things got ugly, Kody claimed, "You've cheated me out of my contact with my family."

Janelle snapped, "It's not my fault, you asked them, you asked them Kody. I have not done anything." She continued, "You asked them who they blame."

Kody replied, "Well, they blame me because you do."

By turning the other sister wives against him, Kody feels Janelle betrayed him. Kody claims that it was she who prompted Meri and Robyn to consider their level of marital happiness.

Are 'Sister Wives' stars Kody Brown and Janelle Brown still together?

'Sister Wives' star Janelle Brown is no longer married to Kody Brown (TLC)

Kody Brown and Janelle Brown are no longer together. Janelle made the decision to end her relationship with Kody after Christine did. The breakdown of Janelle and Kody's marriage was thoroughly filmed for the newest season.

Kody claimed in one of the episodes, "Men don't feel love from women who don't respect them. I feel like Janelle struggles to respect me or show me respect. It might be an unfair statement, I don't know."

As the arguments continued to turn ugly between the estranged couple, Kody said, "If you don't respect me, don't bother with the love. It doesn't work in my world."

Where is 'Sister Wives' star Janelle Brown now?

Janelle is currently spending time with her friends and family. Moreover, she has been traveling a lot these days.

Janelle recently traveled to Mexico. She uploaded a video on Instagram from her Mexico trip saying, "Final evening in Mexico @fairmontmayakoba. It was a beautiful breezy evening on the beach with food, drinks, and entertainment. Perfect way to top off the trip!"

View this post on Instagram A post shared by janellebrown117 (@janellebrown117)

After Mexico Janelle headed to Utah. She wrote, "I’m home and actually on my way up to UT to hang out with Christine, Mykelti, and Aspyn for a fun couple of days."

Apart from meeting friends, focusing on family, and traveling, Janelle is also putting a lot of effort into maintaining the fitness of her body.

'Sister Wives' Season 18 new episodes release every Sunday at 10 pm ET on TLC.
